-------------------------------------------------------------
Abigail Chase: You're treasure hunters, aren't you?

Ben Gates: We're more like treasure protectors.
-------------------------------------------------------------------
Dr. Abigail Chase: So, you believe that there is a treasure on the back
of...

Benjamin Franklin Gates: On the back of the Declaration of Independence.

Dr. Abigail Chase: I'd like to see your proof.

Benjamin Franklin Gates: Uhhh
[pauses to look at Riley, who shakes head no]

Benjamin Franklin Gates: We don't have it.

Dr. Abigail Chase: And who took it? Bigfoot?
-------------------------------------------------------------
Ben: We believe there's an encryption on the back. It's invisible.

Riley: That's where we lost the Department of Homeland Security.
-------------------------------------------------------------
Riley Poole: It's surrounded by guards... video monitors...
and little kids on their eighth grade field trips.
-------------------------------------------------------------
Ben: You don't need someone crazy,
if you're one step short of crazy, what do you get?

Riley: Obsessed?

Ben: Passionate.
-------------------------------------------------------------
Ben: The treasure is a myth.

Ben: Well I refuse to believe that.
-------------------------------------------------------------
Patrick Gates: This better not be about the dumb treasure.
-------------------------------------------------------------
Ben: I just really thought I was going to find the treasure.

Patrick Gates: OK. Then we just keep looking for it.
-------------------------------------------------------------
Riley Poole: Who wants to go down the creepy tunnel inside the tomb first?
-------------------------------------------------------------
Abigail Chase: [referring to the underground staircase]
How did they build all this?

Ben Gates: The same way the built the pyramids

Riley Poole: Right... the aliens helped them
-------------------------------------------------------------
Riley Poole: It's a big blue-ish green man... with a strange goatee
... this must be significant. [hugs the statue]
-------------------------------------------------------------
Benjamin Franklin Gates: [paraphrasing Thomas Edison, about invention of
light bulb] I didn't fail, I found 2,000 ways how not to make a light bulb;
I only need one way to make it work.
-------------------------------------------------------------
Ben Gates: This is the preservation room.
Do you know what they keep in the preservation room?

Riley Poole: Delicious jams and jellies?
-------------------------------------------------------------
Ben: I'll tell you what, the next time we find treasure that redefines
mystery for all man-kind you make the call for the finders fee.
-------------------------------------------------------------
Art Neuendorffer

